      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC896474a8257a10058ca6f04d994144d2"></a>Description of the clutch assembly
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14542"> </a>The clutch is disengaged by a drive unit consisting of a thrust piston (C) accommodated inside a small cap mounted to the
            generator cover. This piston (C) pushes a pushrod (B), which runs through gearbox primary shaft and operates the pressure
            plate&nbsp;(1) located on top of the clutch plate pack (2).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14544"> </a>Drive is transmitted from the crankshaft to the gearbox primary shaft by a gear integrated with the clutch housing/primary
            drive gear pair (A).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14546"> </a>Accommodated in the clutch housing is a set of drive and driven plates (2). When the clutch is operated, the driven plates
            push away a drum (3) which is splined onto the gearbox primary shaft.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e14548"> </a>Before working on the internal clutch parts, check that the clutch operates correctly. Then deal with the problem in a systematic
            manner.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_9_028602020.jpg"></center>
      </div>
